							[1655] cell 'Home Entertainment 4K—the next evolution in high definition. It’s changing entertainment and available with the latest Intel Next Unit of Computing (NUC). step_data.thought: I'm now on the product page for 'Intel NUC Kit NUC6i7KYK Mini PC-no Power Cord'. The product title itself already indicates that it doesn't come with a power cord. To verify this information, I should look at the product details section to see if there's any specific mention about the power cord. Looking at the product details, I can see in the bulleted list under 'Product Quick Look' there's a specific bullet point that states: 'Does not include a power cord (if you need one with a US power cord, purchase Intel NUC Kit NUC6i7KYK Mini PC BOXNUC6I7KYK1)'. This confirms that this specific model (NUC6i7KYK) does not come with a power cord. I have found the answer to the user's question.
step_data.action: stop('The Intel NUC Kit NUC6i7KYK Mini PC does NOT come with a power cord.
